to the editor re the real test of welfare reform still lies ahead by william julius wilson and andrew j cherlin op ed july 13 even without the test of a further economic downturn it is clear that just ending welfare as we know it is not enough although much progress has been made the limitations of welfare reform are already apparent entry level jobs are just the first step true reform means moving people from first job to next job furthering career advancement for the working poor this involves both education and training identifying skills that companies need and taking training modules right into the workplace the challenge is ending poverty as we know it barbara rosenbaum chief executive jewish vocational service boston july 19 2001

